Description: Perform a pushup while moving laterally, resembling an alligator's crawl.
Pull resistance bands towards you while maintaining a stable core for a back workout.
Press resistance bands overhead while standing to target the shoulders.
Hold a weight at chest level and squat down, maintaining an upright torso.
Hold a medicine ball and hinge at the hips, keeping your back flat to target the hamstrings.
Rise onto the balls of your feet to strengthen your calves.
From a bear crawl position, kick one leg through to the opposite side, rotating your body.
Run in place while lifting your knees up to hip level.
Perform pushups with hands on a medicine ball for added core and stability work.
Perform a bent-over row with a kettlebell, alternating sides.
Pull a kettlebell vertically to your chest while keeping elbows high.
Step backward into a lunge position and return to standing for each rep.
Stand with feet wide apart and lift a kettlebell from the ground, focusing on glutes and hamstrings.
Jump continuously over a rotating rope to improve cardiovascular fitness.
Sit with feet elevated and twist from side to side, holding a weight for core strength.
Drop into a pushup, then jump explosively up from a standing position.
Swing a kettlebell overhead while using your hips to generate power.
Hold a medicine ball and perform a squat-to-overhead press in one movement.
Lift a heavy sandbag and throw it over your shoulder for explosive power.
Perform a squat, then jump explosively, landing softly back into a squat.
Lie flat and raise your hands and feet simultaneously to touch above your core.
Jump rope with two rotations per jump for increased intensity.
Crawl on hands and feet, navigating around a set of four corners for coordination.
Lie on your back and raise your hips to strengthen glutes and hamstrings.
